### Unified AI Gateway - Error Handling and Validation Tests
### 
### This test collection validates error handling and validation behavior in the Azure API Management (APIM) 
### 
### Prerequisites (see ReadMe for details):
### 1. Run `azd up` to provision the infrastructure and create the VS Code settings file with all required variables
### 2. Ensure your APIM instance and phi-4 Foundry backends are successfully deployed
###
### Test Coverage:
### - Missing JWT bearer token
### - Invalid API key
### - Server side errors (invalid model configuration, non-existent response ID)
### - Unrecognized path (path validation - 403 Forbidden)
###
### Usage:
### - Click "Send Request" above each request in VS Code with REST Client extension
### - Validate negative scenarios and expected error responses
###
# Variables from VS Code REST Client settings
@apimEndpoint = {{apim_gateway_url}}/unified-ai
@apiVersion = 2025-01-01-preview

# Authentication values from VS Code settings
@apimSubKey = {{apim_subscription_key}}

# Non-existent response ID for error testing
@stdResponseId = resp_07c875e068aee6e600692de1de1828819598cd95d9314b6ad5

###############################################################################
### Error Handling Tests
###############################################################################

### Test: Missing JWT bearer token and API key
### Tests gateway behavior when no authentication is provided (no API key or JWT token)
### Expected Response: 401 Unauthorized with message about providing API key or JWT token
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4.1/chat/completions?api-version={{apiVersion}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4.1",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "This should fail without authentication."
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 50
}

### Test: Invalid API Key
### Tests gateway behavior when an invalid/malformed API key is provided
### Expected Response: 401 Unauthorized with missing key message
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/chat/completions
api-key: invalid_api_key

{
    "model": "gpt-4.1",
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "This should use OpenAI routing, not Gemini"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 30
}

### Test: Invalid JWT Bearer Token
### Tests gateway behavior when an invalid/malformed JWT bearer token is provided
### Expected Response: 401 Unauthorized with invalid/expired token message
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/chat/completions
Authorization: Bearer invalid_jwt_token
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "model": "gpt-4.1",
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "This should fail with invalid JWT"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 30
}

### Test: Invalid Response ID
### Tests gateway behavior when requesting a response with an invalid or non-existent response ID
### Expected Response: 404 Not Found or 400 Bad Request
GET {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses/{{stdResponseId}}?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Test: Invalid Model Configuration (Gemini)
# Tests error handling when requesting an invalid/non-existent Gemini model.
# Expected 500 response: "Backend not configured for the requested model or API type."
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/v1beta/openai/chat/completions
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "model": "gemini-invalid-model",
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "This should fail"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 20
}

### Test: Unrecognized Path (Path Validation)
### Tests gateway behavior when requesting a path that doesn't match any configured API type base-path
### Expected Response: 403 Forbidden with PathNotAllowed error code
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/admin/reset
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "action": "reset"
}

###